FBIS4-27847 "dreas108_c_94007" FBIS-EAS-94-108 Daily Report 5 Jun 1994 North Korea Stage `Provocative' Exercise 3 Jun Stage `Provocative' Exercise 3 Jun SK0506085594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0809 GMT 5 Jun 94 SK0506085594 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists on June 3 staged a provocative bombing exercise against the North in the sky above South Korea by mobilizing 20 odd Pacific-based pursuit-assault planes and VTOL [vertical takeoff and landing] assault planes and various types of fighter-bombers, assault planes, observation planes and reconnaissance planes belonging to the U.S. Airforce present in South Korea and the puppet Airforce, according to military sources. On the same day, a tank group of the puppet Army deployed in the area of Paju County and large-calibre artillery groups of the puppet Army which took positions in Paju County and Chorwon County, South Korean Kangwon Province, fired some 20 tank shells and 120 artillery shells into the area near the demilitarized zone, and armed bandits of the puppet Army in the area fired more than 1,000 large-calibre machinegun and automatic rifle bullets, kicking up war fever. And, "commandoes" dropped on the area of Paju County incited a war atmosphere by making a surprise attack on the targets in their operational plan. Such war exercises of the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean puppets gravely threaten the peace and security of the Korean peninsula.
